      {
        "id": "Q2",
        "Topic": "sum of an ap",
        "subquestion_1": "Sum with last term known ($S_n$ given $a_n$): Calculate the sum of the first $n$ terms ($S_n$) when the first term ($a_1$), common difference ($d$), and the last term ($a_n$) are provided or derivable.",
        "subquestion_2": "Sum using $a_1$ and $d$ ($S_n$ formula): Calculate the sum of the first $n$ terms ($S_n$) using only the first term ($a_1$), the common difference ($d$), and the number of terms ($n$).",
        "subquestion_3": "Sum of a range of terms ($S_m - S_n$): Calculate the sum of terms from the $(m+1)^{th}$ term to the $n^{th}$ term, requiring the calculation of two separate sums."
